⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Bubbles
node MSC · MSC · ⟦The Bubbles:MSC:b78890⟧

WHO   — The Bubbles — the breath-borne weapon and key
WHAT  — The drifting bubbles through which the whole of Milon's Secret Castle is played — blown to pop enemies, and blown against walls, blocks, and scenery to reveal the hidden items, money, doors, and passages within.
WHERE — MSC · Milon's Secret Castle  Framework inputs: Milon's Secret Castle (Hudson Soft, NES 1988)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a boy with no sword and no spell still has breath; because air, made into a thing, can both strike down what blocks the way and break open what hides the way; because every blank wall surely conceals a door, and only a bubble can prove it.
HOW   — By being blown — outward at enemies until they pop, and outward at the castle itself, where a bubble bursting against stone or scenery loosens whatever was hidden behind it.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am only air, given a shape and a breath — but I am the weapon, and I am the key.

spoken token : zar-nond-phaes   ·   hex : b78890
